=== TASK ===
# Loading / Success / Toast Components (Status Pages)

## Overview
Create a lightweight, reusable set of status UI components for asynchronous operations across the app. Include a loading state (spinner and skeletons), a success confirmation modal, and toast notifications for errors, saves, and background job completions. These components should be visually consistent with StudySpark’s design system, accessible, responsive, and easily pluggable into any page or workflow that performs asynchronous actions (data fetches, file uploads, AI generation steps, exports, payments, etc.).

## Page Description (Full Detail)
This page concentrates on the shared status UIs used throughout the app to communicate asynchronous operation states. Goals are to provide immediate, non-intrusive feedback during loading, clear confirmation when an action succeeds, and timely, non-blocking toasts for transient messages. The UI should be:
- Lightweight and non-blocking: avoid blocking user interaction unless necessary (e.g., a critical success confirm with CTA).
- Accessible: proper ARIA roles, labels, focus management, and keyboard navigation.
- Consistently styled: align with the project’s visual language — pastel peach, muted lavender, tangerine accents, rounded shapes, and soft shadows.
- Highly reusable: props-driven customization for content, actions, durations, and variants.
- Easily testable: deterministic rendering with clear states for loading, success, and toast visibility.

UI elements and behavior:
- Loading State
  - Spinner indicator with accessible label (aria-live polite or assertive as appropriate).
  - Optional skeleton loaders for content placeholders.
  - Subtle messaging like “Loading…” with optional descriptive text.
  - Optional timeout or cancel action via a close/abort control if operation supports cancellation.
- Success Modal
  - Centered modal/dialog with a friendly success icon, title, descriptive text, and primary/secondary actions.
  - CTA to view results, download, or navigate to relevant page (configurable via props).
  - Escape/overlay click handling to close when appropriate; focus trap when open.
- Toast Notifications
  - In-app toasts that appear on top or bottom of the screen, non-modal.
  - Support for variants: success, error, info, and warning.
  - Auto-dismiss after a configurable duration with pause on hover/focus.
  - Optional action button within the toast (e.g., “Retry”, “View”) and a close button.
  - Ensure toasts do not stack into overflow; limit visible count or provide scrollable stack.
- Interaction details
  - Animations: subtle, fast transitions for entry/exit; hover states on actionable elements.
  - Keyboard accessibility: all interactive elements reachable via keyboard; focus outlines visible.
  - Visual consistency: use pill-shaped badges, rounded cards, and gradient accents per the design guidelines.

